[Script Info]
; WP-J1 regression sample -- the "gradient band" typesetting idiom.
;
; Verbatim from [Dae] Miss Kobayashi's Dragon Maid S ep02 at media 1116.560s
; (18:36.56), the sign the user reported as "completely messed up, flashes and
; flickers" under --sub-gpu-raster=yes.  ONE full-frame \p1 drawing is drawn 70
; times over, each copy \clip'ed to a different 16px horizontal strip and given
; a slightly different \c, faking a smooth vertical gradient across the shape.
;
; Why it is a regression gate: the rectangular \clip is a dst-space crop, so a
; consumer that sizes a run's coverage from the glyph bbox alone allocates and
; rasterizes the WHOLE drawing 70 times to show 70 thin strips.  At >=1440p that
; overflowed the transient chain (gcache-overcommit > 0 = dropped region-layers,
; a different subset each frame = the flicker).  Gate: gcache-overcommit == 0
; and a temporal A/B vs CPU libass at <= 3/255 across the sign's lifetime.
;
; Drawings only -- no font is required (the pSigns Arial fontname is never used).
ScriptType: v4.00+
WrapStyle: 0
PlayResX: 1920
PlayResY: 1080
ScaledBorderAndShadow: yes
YCbCr Matrix: TV.709

